    {
      "id": "mouse-controls-overview",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Overview",
      "position": {
        "x": -420,
        "y": -420
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 520,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "body": "# Mouse Controls Proposal\n\nThis graph is the planning surface for completing Twilite mouse interaction surfaces (context menus + radial menu + core pointer gestures) with a clear **have vs need** inventory.\n\n## How planning nodes render (why this graph works)\n- Planning nodes (`task`, `goal`, `open-question`, `decision`, `dependency`, `summary`) render via their task-planning **node-class bindings** (\"bridged\" contract-first rendering).\n- If a planning node shows as `UNKNOWN_NODE_TYPE`, it usually means `_classBinding` is missing or mismatched.\n\n## We Have (today)\n\n### Browser (menus)\n- Address bar right-click menu: **Copy**, **Paste & Go**, **Copy Web-Friendly URL** (`components/Browser/Browser.js`).\n- Home button right-click menu: **Template gallery**, **Set Home**, **Clear Home** (`components/Browser/Browser.js`).\n\n### Graph Editor (menus)\n- Node right-click menu: **Run Node**, **Open Definition** (`components/GraphEditor/GraphEditorContent.js`).\n- Radial menu exists (premium editor): layout + view toggles + quick-add (`components/GraphEditor/components/RadialMenu.js`).\n\n### Graph Editor (mouse controls already present)\n- Node dragging (left mouse), selection, marquee selection, pan/zoom infrastructure (via NodeGraph layers and event handlers).\n\n## We Need (proposal)\n\n### Context menus (minimum baseline)\n**Graph canvas/background**\n- Paste at cursor (graph clipboard)\n- Add node at cursor (quick add)\n- Fit to content, layout/beautify, reroute edges\n- Toggle: grid, snap-to-grid, minimap, properties panel\n- Document properties\n\n**Node**\n- Copy / Cut / Paste (selection-aware)\n- Duplicate, Delete\n- Open properties\n- Lock / Unlock\n- Style shortcuts (color, label visibility)\n- Group / Ungroup\n- Keep: Run Node, Open Definition\n\n**Edge**\n- Delete\n- Routing/style options\n- Label edit/toggle\n- Open properties\n\n**Group**\n- Rename\n- Color\n- Ungroup / Delete\n- Fit/zoom to group\n\n**Browser address bar parity**\n- Cut\n- Paste (without navigating)\n- Select All\n- Optional: Undo/Redo (when supported)\n- Clipboard-permission failure UX (toast + keyboard hint)\n\n### Radial menu (high-frequency only)\n- Own 8–16 actions that benefit from spatial memory (fast, repeatable)\n- Avoid duplicating full context menus\n- Clearly define invocation (right-click background vs hotkey vs hold) and selection interaction\n\n### Mouse gestures / controls (baseline)\n- Right-click: target-aware context menu\n- Drag: pan, node move (edit-only), marquee selection\n- Wheel: cursor-centered zoom\n- Double-click: open properties (node/edge/group)\n- Optional: middle-click pan, space-drag pan\n\n## Deliverable\nA single coherent mouse-control system:\n- Context menus cover completeness + discoverability\n- Radial menu covers speed for the most common actions\n- Clipboard contract makes copy/paste predictable across nodes/edges/groups\n\n---\n\nTasks in this graph break the work down into implementable steps and keep the key decisions/questions explicit."
      }
    },
