      "data": {
        "body": "Decide which actions belong in the radial menu vs context menus so we avoid duplication and keep discoverability.\n\nProposed rule:\n- Radial menu: 8–16 highest-frequency actions with strong spatial memory value.\n- Context menus: complete, target-aware lists including less frequent actions.\n- Toolbar: persistent controls + global state.\n",
        "status": "open",
        "options": [
          "Radial menu is primary for high-frequency actions; context menus remain complete.",
          "Context menus are primary; radial menu is limited to layout/view toggles.",
          "Hybrid: radial menu for global actions; context menus for object-specific actions."
        ],
        "definitionKey": "decision",
        "_classBinding": {
