    {
      "id": "mouse-controls-clipboard-contract-doc",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Clipboard Contract (Current)",
      "position": {
        "x": 1280,
        "y": 940
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 520,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "body": "# Clipboard Contract (Current)\n\nThis is the **current** clipboard payload shape used by the graph editor shortcuts (`components/GraphEditor/hooks/useGraphShortcuts.js`). Paste is handled through `pasteFromClipboardUnified` → `pasteHandler` → `pasteGraphData`.\n\n## Decisions (for context menu work)\n- **Selection policy:** preserve selection on right-click (multi-select context actions).\n- **Paste semantics:** context-menu paste should be **paste-at-cursor**; keyboard paste can remain viewport/anchor based.\n- **Groups:** excluded for now (group concept will be revisited separately).\n- **System nodes:** should **not** be copied by default.\n\n## Primary payload: `nodegraph-data`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"nodegraph-data\",\n  \"action\": \"add\",\n  \"nodes\": [/* node objects */],\n  \"edges\": [/* edge objects */],\n  \"clusters\": [/* group objects (optional) */],\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-02T00:00:00.000Z\",\n  \"nodeCount\": 3,\n  \"edgeCount\": 2\n}\n```\n\n### Notes\n- `action` is optional; when present, supported values include `add` and `replace` (see `handlers/graphEditorHandlers.js`).\n- Nodes *may* omit `position`; paste handler hydrates positions and can trigger an auto-layout when positions are missing.\n- Copy shortcut currently includes:\n  - selected nodes\n  - edges whose `source` and `target` are both selected\n  - (groups are not currently included by the shortcut copy)\n\n## Alternative payload: CRUD command list\n\nThe paste handler also supports JSON that represents **Graph CRUD commands** (transaction/batch patterns). This is used by some advanced flows and plugin-like interactions.\n\n## System node remap policy (paste)\n\nWhen pasting payloads that include system nodes (manifest/declaration/legend/dictionary), the paste handler may remap IDs to existing system nodes in the destination graph rather than creating duplicates.\n\n## Gaps vs desired future (clipboard)\n- Add paste-at-cursor semantics for context-menu paste.\n- Define explicit \"copy system nodes\" advanced action (if ever needed).\n- Document ID remap strategy for nodes/edges on duplicate/paste.\n"
      }
    },
